POLICE are investigating the deaths of six buzzards which were found in a field. Six buzzards found dead POLICE are investigating the deaths of six buzzards which were found in a field.The birds of prey were discovered in the Fourdoun area of Aberdeenshire at about 3.30pm on Tuesday.The field where they were found is around one mile north-west of Fordoun on an unclassified road leading from Fordoun to Auchenblae.